Usage: createSdpGroup [-help] [-justifyBy <SW|SE|NW|NE|N|W|S|E|MID>]
                      -name <sdpGroupName> [-type <row|col|space>] {{-skip_space <val> } | -skip_space_by_site_width <val> <siteName> | -skip_space_by_micron <val>} | {{{-inst <WCardName...> [-keepOrder ]} | -selected } [[-spread_group <val> ] | [-spread_group_by_site_width <val> <siteName>] | [-spread_group_by_micron <val>] | [[-numRow <val>] [-numCol <val>] ]]}

-help                                    # Prints out the command usage
-inst <WCardName...>                     # wild card instance name
                                         # (string, optional)
-justifyBy <SW|SE|NW|NE|N|W|S|E|MID>     # justify by direction
                                         # (string, optional)
-keepOrder                               # honor the instance order in the
                                         # input sdp instance list
                                         # (bool, optional)
-name <sdpGroupName>                     # name of the group to be created
                                         # (string, required)
-numCol <val>                            # number of column to be created
                                         # (int, optional)
-numRow <val>                            # number of row to be created
                                         # (int, optional)
-selected                                # selected instances (bool, optional)
-skip_space <val>                        # number of row/column space
                                         # (string, optional)
-skip_space_by_micron <val>              # skip space is in unit microns
                                         # (string, optional)
-skip_space_by_site_width <val> <siteName>
                                         # number of row/column space and name
                                         # of tech site. use the width of site
                                         # as skip unit in horizontal direction
                                         # (list, optional)
-spread_group <val>                      # spread group using skip space
                                         # (string, optional)
-spread_group_by_micron <val>            # spread group in unit microns
                                         # (string, optional)
-spread_group_by_site_width <val> <siteName>
                                         # number of row/column space and name
                                         # of tech site. Use the width of site
                                         # as skip unit in horizontal direction
                                         # (list, optional)
-type <row|col|space>                    # record type (string, optional)